  <h1>Playtiss</h1>
  <p class="meta">A collaboration space for humans and AI</p>

  <p>The Collaboration Protocol's working implementation. Where the protocol's axioms — <em>no party owns the truth alone</em>, <em>no errors only exceptions</em>, <em>collaboration with the world</em>, <em>change and projection are equal</em> — become a running substrate that humans and AI can actually use to build together.</p>

  <h2>What Playtiss makes possible</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Compose, don't follow.</strong> Tasks aren't rigid SOPs. Each step carries an intention, not a fixed procedure. Revision history is first-class, so changes propagate without breaking upstream work.</li>
    <li><strong>Switch substrates without losing continuity.</strong> Run a step on Claude today, swap to Gemini tomorrow, drop in a local open-source model when data sensitivity demands it. The collaboration stays consistent; the model layer is transport.</li>
    <li><strong>Across vendors, across tools, across people.</strong> Multiple humans and multiple AIs share the same collaboration space without any one party claiming the truth.</li>
    <li><strong>Locally deployable.</strong> For compliance-sensitive verticals — legal, healthcare, financial services — Playtiss runs on your own infrastructure with whatever local LLM you choose. Data never has to leave.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Status</h2>

  <p>MIT-licensed core: <code>@playtiss/core</code> — the protocol's vocabulary as TypeScript types (Channel, Schema, Actor, Action, Task, Revision). Multi-agent runtime is in active development; alpha releases tracked on GitHub.</p>

  <p><a href="https://github.com/WujiLabs/playtiss">github.com/WujiLabs/playtiss</a> · <code>npm install @playtiss/core</code></p>
